HEADWORD: Potheen
<hw>Po*theen"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ir. <ets>poitin</ets> a small pot, whisky
made in private stills; cf. <ets>pota</ets> pot, fr. E.
<ets>pot</ets>.]</ety> <def>Whisky; especially whisky distilled in a
small way privately or illicitly by the Irish peasantry.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>potteen</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

